%N A393835 Lexicographically earliest sequence of distinct nonnegative integers such that for any n >= 0, A393834(n, a(n)) = 1.
%C A393835 A self-inverse permutation of the nonnegative integers.
%C A393835 This sequence is to A393834 what A004488 is to A153490.
%H A393835 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A393835/b393835.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..6560</a>
